columns.name: name
columns.description: The friendly name of the Load Balancer that was provided during resource creation.

columns.name: arn
columns.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the load balancer.

columns.name: scheme
columns.description: The load balancing scheme of load balancer.

columns.name: canonical_hosted_zone_id
columns.description: The ID of the Amazon Route 53 hosted zone associated with the load balancer.

columns.name: vpc_id
columns.description: The ID of the VPC for the load balancer.

columns.name: created_time
columns.description: The date and time the load balancer was created.

columns.name: customer_owned_ipv4_pool
columns.description: The ID of the customer-owned address pool.

columns.name: dns_name
columns.description: The public DNS name of the load balancer.

columns.name: ip_address_type
columns.description: The type of IP addresses used by the subnets for your load balancer.

columns.name: state_code
columns.description: Current state of the load balancer.

columns.name: availability_zones
columns.description: The subnets for the load balancer.

columns.name: security_groups
columns.description: The IDs of the security groups for the load balancer.

columns.name: load_balancer_attributes
columns.description: The AWS account ID of the image owner.

columns.name: tags_src
columns.description: A list of tags attached to the load balancer.
